HEADWORD: launcher
<hw>launcher</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a device capable of
launching a rocket.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> rocket launcher.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A device which launches aircraft from an aircraft
carrier; -- it provides additional velocity to the airplane, to
supplement that from the airplane's engines, so that the airplane
rapidly achieves a velocity sufficient to sustain it in flight when
taking off.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> catapult.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>launching</ent>⟦br⟧
